# GitHub Best Practices

- Keep commits focused, small, and reviewable.
- Never commit secrets, tokens, credentials, or personal data.
- Use clear commit messages that explain intent.
- Prefer PR-friendly changes and include validation notes when relevant.
- Do not rewrite published history unless explicitly requested.
- Do not force-push to protected/default branches unless explicitly requested.
- Do not use destructive git commands unless explicitly requested.
- Keep generated artifacts and local build outputs out of version control.
- Verify author identity before committing/pushing.
- Confirm branch status (`git status`) before commit and after commit.

## Local Artifact Guardrails

Treat these as local-only by default:
- `.vcpkg/`
- `.skse-menu-framework-2/`
- `.knockout-ext/`
- `build/`
- `build-commonlib/`
- `build-vs/`
- `release-staging/`

